Or official docs:
üëâ ActiveSupport Core Extensions

Interview killer line üß†

ActiveSupport extends Ruby core classes like String, Hash, Array, Time, and Numeric with convenience methods for formatting, time calculations, key transformations, and presence checks, making Rails code more expressive.